<item>
            <title>[HADOOP-10496] Metrics system FileSink can leak file descriptor.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-10496</link>
                <project id="12310240" key="HADOOP">Hadoop Common</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;FileSink&lt;/tt&gt; opens a file.  If the &lt;tt&gt;MetricsSystem&lt;/tt&gt; is shutdown, then the sink is discarded and the file is never closed, causing a file descriptor leak.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12708150">HADOOP-10496</key>
            <summary>Metrics system FileSink can leak file descriptor.</summary>
