                            <comment id="13967881" author="cnauroth" created="Sun, 13 Apr 2014 16:32:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I found this bug during runs of &lt;tt&gt;TestFileSink&lt;/tt&gt; on Windows.  The test concludes by trying to delete the output file.  On Windows, the delete fails, because the file is still held open and locked.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here is a patch that fixes it.  &lt;tt&gt;MetricsSink&lt;/tt&gt; is public, and there can be custom implementations in the wild.  I didn&apos;t want to introduce a backwards-incompatibility by defining a &lt;tt&gt;close&lt;/tt&gt; method right on the &lt;tt&gt;MetricsSink&lt;/tt&gt; interface.  Instead, this patch adds JavaDocs to &lt;tt&gt;MetricsSink&lt;/tt&gt; stating that implementations also may optionally implement &lt;tt&gt;Closeable&lt;/tt&gt;, and then &lt;tt&gt;MetricsSinkAdapter&lt;/tt&gt; does an instanceof check and calls close.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I verified on Mac and Windows.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
